    en: "NY law lets a home buyer or renter ask the utility for a written history of the property's past gas, electric, or steam costs before signing. The Truth in Heating Law (Public Service Law section 75) requires every regulated NY utility to provide 24 months of cost data on request, in writing, within 5 business days, at no charge. The current owner or tenant can ask without anyone else's permission. A prospective buyer or renter can ask with the current occupant's consent. The data shows monthly consumption (kWh, therms) and dollar costs. The information helps reveal hidden heating, cooling, and electric costs that are not part of the asking price."
